    title: "Netflix’s next TV gaming experiment will scare the hell out of you",
    summary: "As part of the latest evolution of its gaming initiative, Netflix has made a big push into cloud-based games you can play on your TV, much in the same way you'd watch a movie or show on the service. So far, these games have been pretty tame. Things like trivia, party games, and a weirdly [&#8230;]",
    body: "As part of the latest evolution of its gaming initiative, Netflix has made a big push into cloud-based games you can play on your TV , much in the same way you'd watch a movie or show on the service. So far, these games have been pretty tame. Things like trivia, party games, and a weirdly dated FIFA . But Netflix's next release goes in a completely different direction: It's an interactive horror experience that's gruesome, terrifying, and quite possibly the future of the company's gaming efforts.\n\nThe new game is called Unhinged , and it launches on Netflix on June 30th. It's developed by Night School Studio, which is best known for the Strange …",
